UML:TaggedValue.value: The Analysis Model is the realization of the Use Case model. It can consists of Communication diagrams that realize each Use Case defined in the Use Case Model.

The Domain Model is a view of all the objects that make up an area of interest, and their relationships. It is used to capture the significant objects within a system, organization or any target domain.
This is a Use Case realization of "Use Case 1" defined in the Use Case Model. This includes a Communication diagram with Boundary, Entity and Control Objects.
